{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolygon","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MLNMultiPoint"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object. Configure the appearance of an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s polygons collectively using an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:"},{"type":"text","text":" method. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}]},{"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples","type":"heading","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object from an array of coordinates.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherited By","type":"inheritedBy"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNEmptyFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygonFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolylineFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolylineFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointC